embeds.title: Spreading Slime
embeds.description:
Uncommon Power / 2 :e_slime: / The Slime Boss / Downfall

Effects that apply **Goop** :p_goop: apply 2 (3) more.

messages.content: One of the better tackles, but that's largely because it's a very solid payoff for the goop decks. It's easy to take early in a run to help deal burst damage in act 1, and it can be used effectively later in the run to get double the benefit out of goop stacking. You will generally know when you want this, but it's even a fairly safe pick early in the run when your deck is still shaping up.

On a side note, I do wish tackles had a bit more support, it's a cool theme, and I really like that the damage can be mitigated by blocking first, but there just aren't very many ways to make them into a real archetype. You can make them deal a little bit more damage with flame tackle and the power, and you can make it so that you don't take damage from the next few tackles with that common, but there's no great way to help them become a real part of a block/draw/energy engine.
It'd be better if it had retain on it so you can use it as a panic button
